== Overview

This document applies the three core requirements validation techniques introduced in the
Requirements Engineering lecture — completeness checking, consistency checking, and realism
checking — to the requirements governing Team B's Missing Dependencies feature.

The goal of validation is not to obtain approval from stakeholders but to ensure that the
system-to-be correctly reflects domain relationships and user needs. Each section below walks
through one validation check against concrete walkthroughs, documents what was observed when
those walkthroughs were executed against the running system, and records the outcome — including
any requirement gaps, contradictions, or untestable statements that were identified and addressed.

The requirements examined in this report are drawn from the following sections of the project
Proposal document:

* Section 2.3 — Domain Requirements (DR-1 through DR-10)
* Section 2.3.3 — Interface Requirements
* Section 2.3.4 — Machine Requirements
